{"enabled": true, "name": "Client Handover - Data Prep", "description": "PHASE 1 of 2: Extract and organize IPA data by documentation sections. Handles 1-N LPD files per RICE item. After completion, trigger 'Client Handover - Analysis' hook to generate report. Split workflow prevents context accumulation crashes.", "version": "1", "when": {"type": "userTriggered"}, "newSession": true, "then": {"type": "askAgent", "prompt": "IPA Client Handover Documentation - PHASE 1: Data Preparation\n\nThis is PHASE 1 of a 2-phase workflow. After this completes, you will trigger PHASE 2 (Analysis) hook.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nWHY TWO PHASES?\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSequential subagent execution accumulates context (80+ KB by subagent #3).\nSplitting into two phases ensures PHASE 2 starts with clean context.\n\nPHASE 1 (This Hook): Extract + Organize data (Python-heavy, no subagents)\nPHASE 2 (Next Hook): Launch subagents + Generate report (clean context)\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nWORKFLOW - PHASE 1\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nSTEP 0: CLEAN TEMP FOLDER\n\nExecute PowerShell:\nRemove-Item Temp/* -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\n\nSTEP 1-5: USER SELECTION\n\n1. List clients in Projects/ → User selects\n2. List RICE items → User selects\n3. List *.lpd files → User selects ALL (multi-select)\n4. Check for *.docx (spec) and *_log.txt (WU log)\n5. Confirm selection → User confirms\n\nSTEP 6-10: PROCESS EACH LPD\n\nFOR EACH selected LPD file:\n\nSTEP 6: EXTRACT DATA (Python)\n\n# Extract LPD data\nexecutePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_lpd_data import extract_lpd_data; extract_lpd_data(['<lpd_path>'], 'Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json')\\\"\")\n\n# Extract spec data (if available and first iteration)\nIf spec file exists AND first LPD:\n    executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_spec import extract_spec; extract_spec('<spec_path>', 'Temp/<RICEItem>_spec_data.json')\\\"\")\n\n# Extract WU log data (if available)\nIf WU log exists for this process:\n    executePwsh(\"python -c \\\"from ReusableTools.IPA_Analyzer.extract_wu_log import extract_wu_log; extract_wu_log('<wu_log_path>', 'Temp/<ProcessName>_wu_data.json')\\\"\")\n\nVerify: executePwsh(\"Test-Path Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json\")\n\nSTEP 7: ORGANIZE BY SECTIONS (Python)\n\nexecutePwsh(\"python ReusableTools/IPA_ClientHandover/organize_by_sections.py Temp/<ProcessName>_lpd_data.json <spec_json_or_none> <wu_json_or_none> Temp/<ProcessName>\")\n\nCreates 5 section files:\n- Temp/<ProcessName>_section_business.json\n- Temp/<ProcessName>_section_workflow.json\n- Temp/<ProcessName>_section_configuration.json\n- Temp/<ProcessName>_section_activities.json\n- Temp/<ProcessName>_section_validation.json\n\nEND FOR EACH\n\nShow progress: \"✓ Processed <N> of <Total> LPD files\"\n\nSTEP 11: DONE - TRIGGER PHASE 2\n\nShow summary:\n✓ Data extraction complete\n✓ Processes prepared: <ProcessName1>, <ProcessName2>, ...\n✓ Section files created: 5 per process\n\nNEXT STEP: Trigger 'Client Handover - Analysis' hook to generate report.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nCRITICAL RULES\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n1. NO SUBAGENTS IN PHASE 1\n   - Only Python extraction and organization\n   - No AI analysis in this phase\n   - Keeps context minimal\n\n2. VERIFY FILES CREATED\n   - Check each section file exists (Test-Path)\n   - If any missing, STOP and report error\n\n3. MULTI-PROCESS SUPPORT\n   - Handle 1-N LPD files\n   - Create section files for each process\n   - All processes analyzed in PHASE 2\n\n4. CLEAN HANDOFF TO PHASE 2\n   - Save process names for PHASE 2\n   - Save client and RICE item names\n   - PHASE 2 will load section files with clean context"}}
